archimate:DataObject.name: SignalingProtocol
archimate:DataObject.documentation: This is an abstract base class for representing different types of signaling protocols that can be managed. Signaling protocols are used to convey information along a specific path. This class represents a convenient aggregation point for defining how signaling protocols are managed and used. The SID model defines COPS and RSVP as examples of subclasses of this class.
